HEADWORD: Terete
<hw>Te*rete"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>teres</ets>,
<ets>-etis</ets>, rounded off, properly, rubbed off, fr.
<ets>terere</ets> to rub.]</ety> <def>Cylindrical and slightly tapering;
columnar, as some stems of plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

